User:

1. A front-end web app in Python which lets you vote between two options
2. A Redis which collects new votes
3. A .NET worker which consumes votes and stores them inâ€¦
4. A Postgres database backed by a Docker volume
5. A Node.js web app which shows the results of the voting in real time


1. Python - Vote
2. Redis - 
3. .NET - Worker
4. Postgres
5. Node - Result

$ docker run --name vote-redis -d redis redis-server --save 60 1 --loglevel warning


Vote App Setup Steps:
----------------------
1. Build an Images
- Vote
docker build -t vote:v1 .

- Worker
docker build -t worker:v1 .

- Result
docker build -t result:v1 .

2. Redis Container Run
docker run -d --name redis -h redis redis

3. Postgres Container Run
docker run -d --name postgres -h postgres -e POSTGRES_USER=postgres -e POSTGRES_PASSWORD=postgres postgres

4. Vote Container Run and Link with Redis
docker run -d --name vote -p 2000:80 --link redis:redis vote:v1

5. Worker Container Run and Link with Redis and Postgres
docker run -d --name worker --link redis:redis --link postgres:db worker:v1

6. Result Container Run and link with Postgres
docker run -d --name result -p 4000:4000 --link postgres:db  result:v1

